reviewText: This is really a wonderful find. It has Diane Reeves in her EARLY YEARS as the shining star that she has become. I enjoyed the progressive jazz song done with Diane Reeve's back up band "A Fine Madness" titled "The Holmes," which sounds like RTF (the  electric piano & drums) meets Weather Report (the synth, bass, & percussion). Billy Carrol on bass was INCREDIBLE and the talking drum on the song "The Holmes was cool!
It was wonderful for "back in the day".  Good start for her.
